593// Apply a matrix rotation to each ARGB pixel.
594// matrix_argb is 4 signed ARGB values. -128 to 127 representing -2 to 2.
595// The first 4 coefficients apply to B, G, R, A and produce B of the output.
596// The next 4 coefficients apply to B, G, R, A and produce G of the output.
597// The next 4 coefficients apply to B, G, R, A and produce R of the output.
598// The last 4 coefficients apply to B, G, R, A and produce A of the output.
599LIBYUV_API
600int ARGBColorMatrix(const uint8_t* src_argb,
601 int src_stride_argb,
602 uint8_t* dst_argb,
603 int dst_stride_argb,
604 const int8_t* matrix_argb,
605 int width,
606 int height);
607
608// Deprecated. Use ARGBColorMatrix instead.
609// Apply a matrix rotation to each ARGB pixel.
610// matrix_argb is 3 signed ARGB values. -128 to 127 representing -1 to 1.
611// The first 4 coefficients apply to B, G, R, A and produce B of the output.
612// The next 4 coefficients apply to B, G, R, A and produce G of the output.
613// The last 4 coefficients apply to B, G, R, A and produce R of the output.
614LIBYUV_API
615int RGBColorMatrix(uint8_t* dst_argb,
616 int dst_stride_argb,
617 const int8_t* matrix_rgb,
618 int dst_x,
619 int dst_y,
620 int width,
621 int height);
622
623// Apply a color table each ARGB pixel.
624// Table contains 256 ARGB values.
625LIBYUV_API
626int ARGBColorTable(uint8_t* dst_argb,

629 int dst_x,

634// Apply a color table each ARGB pixel but preserve destination alpha.

636LIBYUV_API
637int RGBColorTable(uint8_t* dst_argb,

639 const uint8_t* table_argb,
640 int dst_x,
641 int dst_y,
642 int width,
643 int height);
644
645// Apply a luma/color table each ARGB pixel but preserve destination alpha.
646// Table contains 32768 values indexed by [Y][C] where 7 it 7 bit luma from
647// RGB (YJ style) and C is an 8 bit color component (R, G or B).
648LIBYUV_API
649int ARGBLumaColorTable(const uint8_t* src_argb,
650 int src_stride_argb,
651 uint8_t* dst_argb,
652 int dst_stride_argb,
653 const uint8_t* luma,
654 int width,
655 int height);
656
657// Apply a 3 term polynomial to ARGB values.
658// poly points to a 4x4 matrix. The first row is constants. The 2nd row is
659// coefficients for b, g, r and a. The 3rd row is coefficients for b squared,
660// g squared, r squared and a squared. The 4rd row is coefficients for b to
661// the 3, g to the 3, r to the 3 and a to the 3. The values are summed and
662// result clamped to 0 to 255.
663// A polynomial approximation can be dirived using software such as 'R'.
664
665LIBYUV_API
666int ARGBPolynomial(const uint8_t* src_argb,
667 int src_stride_argb,
668 uint8_t* dst_argb,
669 int dst_stride_argb,
670 const float* poly,
671 int width,
672 int height);
